'''Government of the Ukrainian People's Republic in exile''', or '''State Center of the Ukrainian People's Republic (SC of UPR)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zakon5.rada.gov.ua/laws/show/314-19|title=Закон України «Про правовий статус та вшанування пам'яті борців за незалежність України у XX столітті»|accessdate=25 липня 2016|archive-date=21 вересня 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170921100540/http://zakon5.rada.gov.ua/laws/show/314-19}}</ref>''' – a set of legislative and executive Ukrainian [[Government in exile|authorities]], which due to Bolshevik aggression and the formation of the [[Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic|USSR]] were partially (in late [[1919]]), and as of late [[1920]] – completely outside of the [[Ukrainian People's Republic|UPR]], on the territory of the [[Second Polish Republic|Republic of Poland]] in [[Tarnów|Tarnow]] (some institutions were located in [[Częstochowa|Czestochowa]]); later on the government agencies operated in [[Warsaw]], [[Paris]], [[Weimar]], [[Bad Kissingen|Kissingen]], [[Munich]], and [[Philadelphia]]. The 10th Emergency Session of the Ukrainian National Council recognized the state of Ukraine as the successor of the Ukrainian People's Republic in exile and agreed to transfer the powers and attributes of state power to the newly elected President of Ukraine.<ref name="МП3">''Плав'юк М.'' [http://history.org.ua/?termin=DC_UNR Державний центр УНР на еміграції (ДЦ УНР)] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817145856/http://history.org.ua/?termin=DC_UNR|date=17 серпня 2016}}</ref>

== Legal basis ==
The legal basis of the UPR government was set in the laws "On the temporary Supreme Administration and Legislation in the UPR" and "On the State People's Council", approved on November 12, [[1920]] by the [[Directorate of Ukraine]]. These acts, based on the laws of the Labor Congress of Ukraine, transferred legislative functions and control over the government of the Ukrainian People's Republic to the State People's Council.

However, prior to the convening of this Council, its functions were assigned to the [[Council of People's Ministers]], and the head of the Directorate acted as the head of state, approving laws, treaties, appointments, representation before foreign states. The head of the Directorate, in case of impossibility to perform duties, was represented by the board, and in case of impossibility to convene it – by the chairman of the Council of People's Ministers.

== Structure ==

* Executive bodies – President (in 1921-1944 - Chief [[Ataman|Otaman]]), the Council of Ministers (1921-1992)
* Legislative bodies – Republic's Council, Ukrainian National Council

